main event: A report of a UFO sighting in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania in 1957.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force, but the information provided was not sufficient for a scientific investigation.
The Air Force requested the witness to submit any additional information, including photographic evidence, to enable a more thorough re-examination of the case.
The report indicates that the witness had taken photographs of the UFO, but the photographs were not available at the time of the report.
The report suggests that the Air Force was interested in obtaining photographic evidence to help reach a more definitive conclusion about the sighting.
The witness was urged to provide the photographic evidence to aid the investigation, as such evidence is often crucial for adequate scientific evaluation.
